pwd – Shows current working directory
ls – Lists files and folders
cd – Changes directory
mkdir – Creates a new directory
rmdir – Removes an empty directory
rm – Deletes files or folders
cp – Copies files or directories
mv – Moves or renames files
cat – Displays file content
head – Shows first few lines of a file
tail – Shows last few lines of a file
less – Views file page by page
ps – Shows running processes
top – Displays live process activity
kill – Terminates a process
whoami – Shows current user
date – Displays current date and time
uname – Shows system information
grep – Searches text in files
find – Finds files in directories
echo – Prints text on screen
clear – Clears terminal screen
history – Shows previous commands
